{
  "texts": [
    "Consider two nn-actuators, one with 3 possible states (off = 1, transition = 0, on = 2), and the other with 2 possible states (off = 1, on = 2).",
    "This results in six switchboard states -11, 12, 01, 02, 21, and 22.",
    "First, we parse through the normal training dataset and copy the time index, sensor reading, nn-actuators (see first four columns in example TABLE 2).",
    "Next, we append a switchboard state (for nn-actuator(s)), at each time index t. This is called the pretrain-sb dataset (see additional column labeled Switchboard in TABLE 2).",
    "Next, for the baby-step method, we compute the difference (diff) between consecutive sensor values and append it to a new column."
  ]
}